ics \u2013 Women's discus throw|1992]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1988SummerOlympics}}\n\nThe '''[[Discus throw|Women's Discus Throw]]''' event at the '''[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Seoul, South Korea]] had an entrylist of 22 competitors, with two qualifying groups before the final (12) took place on Thursday September 29, 1988.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1988/ATH/womens-discus-throw.html |title=Athletics at the 1988 Seoul Summer Games: Women's Discus Throw |accessdate=14 January 2018 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Martina Hellmann]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Diana Gansky]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Tsvetanka Khristova]]|BUL|1988 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing World and Olympic records (in metres) prior to the 1988 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- \n! World Record\n| 76.80\n| {{flagicon|GDR}} [[Gabriele Reinsch]]\n| [[Neubrandenburg]] ([[East Germany|GDR]])\n| July 9, 1988\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 69.96\n| {{flagicon|GDR}} [[Evelin Jahl]]\n| [[Moscow]] ([[Soviet Union|URS]])\n| August 1, 1980\n|}\n\nThe following Olympic record was set during this competition.\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|-\n!Date !! Event !! Athlete !! Distance !! OR !! WR\n|-\n|September 29, 1988||Final ||align=left| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Martina Hellmann]]|GDR|1988 Summer}} || '''72.30m'''|| OR ||\n|}\n\n==Qualifying round==\n*Held on Wednesday September 28, 1988\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!RANK\n!style=\"width: 20em\"|GROUP A\n!style=\"width: 5em\"|DISTANCE\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|1.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Zde\u0148ka \u0160il