</ref>\n|electorate = 174,507 (2016)<ref name=\"comelec\">{{cite web|url=https://www.comelec.gov.ph/php-tpls-attachments/2016NLE/Statistics/Philippine2016VotersProfile/Philippine_2016_Voter_Profile_by_Provinces_and_Cities_or_Municipalities_including_Districts.xlsx |title=Philippines 2016 Voters Profile |publisher=[[Commission on Elections (Philippines)]] |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n|area = 399.14 km\u00b2\n|towns = {{Collapsible list\n| titlestyle = font-weight:normal;text-align:left;background-color:WhiteSmoke;\n| title = 6 [[Local government in the Philippines|LGU]]s\n| '''Municipalities'''\n| [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]]\n| [[Lobo, Batangas|Lobo]]\n| [[Mabini, Batangas|Mabini]]\n| [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]]\n| [[San Pascual, Batangas|San Pascual]]\n| [[Tingloy, Batangas|Tingloy]]\n}}\n|year = 1907\n|members_label = Representative\n|members = [[Raneo Abu]]\n|blank1_name = Political party\n|blank1_info = {{Color box|{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[Nacionalista Party|Nacionalista]]\n|blank2_name = Congressional bloc\n|blank2_info = Majority\n}}\n'''Batangas's 2nd congressional district''' is one of the six [[congressional districts of the Philippines]] in the province of [[Batangas]]. It has been represented in the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] since 1916 and earlier in the [[Philippine Assembly]] from 1907 to 1916.<ref name\"congleg\">{{cite web|url=http://www.congress.gov.ph/legislators/?v=province |title=Roster of Philippine legislators |publisher=[[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> The district consists of the southern Batangas municipalities of [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]], [[Lobo, Batangas|Lobo]], [[Mabini, Batangas|Mabini]], [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]], [[San Pascual, Batangas|San Pascual]] and [[Tingloy, Batangas|Tingloy]]. It is currently represented in the [[18th Congress of the Philippines|18th Congress]] by [[Raneo Abu]] of the [[Nacionalista Party]] (NP).<ref name=\"congmem\">{{cite web|url=http://www.congress.gov.ph/members/ |title=House Members |publisher=[[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Representation history==\n{| class=wikitable \n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | #\n! rowspan=\"2\" colspan=2 | Member\n! colspan=2 | Term of office\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Legislature\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Party\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Electoral history\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Constituent<br/>[[Local government in the Philippines|LGU]]s\n|-\n!Start!!End\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n==='''Batangas's 2nd district for the [[Philippine Assembly]]'''===\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | District created April 1, 1907.<ref>{{cite book|last=Division of Insular Affairs |others=Elihu Root, Secretary of War|title=Eighth Annual Report of the Philippine Commission to the Secretary of War |url=https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=q3tQAAAAYAAJ |accessdate=16 April 2020 |series=Elihu Root Collection of United States Documents Relating to the Philippine Islands|volume=253|year=1908|publisher=United States War Department|location=Washington, D.C.|page=49}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1'''\n| style=\"background:{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Eusebio Orense\n| October 16, 1907\n| October 16, 1909\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[1st Philippine Legislature|1st]]\n| [[Nacionalista Party|Nacionalista]]\n| [[1907 Philippine Assembly elections|Elected in 1907]].\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1907\u20131909'''<br/>[[Batangas City|Batangas]], [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]], [[Cuenca, Batangas|Cuenca]], [[Ibaan]], [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''2'''\n| style=\"background:{{Progresista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Florencio R. Caedo\n| October 16, 1909\n| October 16, 1912\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[2nd Philippine Legislature|2nd]]\n| [[Progresista Party|Progresista]]\n| [[1909 Philippine Assembly elections|Elected in 1909]].\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1909\u20131916'''<br/>[[Alitagtag]], [[Batangas City|Batangas]], [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]], [[Cuenca, Batangas|Cuenca]], [[Ibaan]], [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | ''3'''\n| style=\"background:{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Marcelo Caringal\n| October 16, 1912\n| October 16, 1916\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[3rd Philippine Legislature|3rd]]\n| [[Nacionalista Party|Nacionalista]]\n| [[1912 Philippine Assembly elections|Elected in 1912]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n==='''Batangas's 2nd district for the House of Representatives of the Philippine Islands'''===\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''4'''\n| style=\"background:{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Pablo Borb\u00f3n\n| October 16, 1916\n| June 3, 1919\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[4th Philippine Legislature|4th]]\n| [[Nacionalista Party|Nacionalista]]\n| [[1916 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 1916]].\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1916\u20131919'''<br/>[[Alitagtag]], [[Batangas City|Batangas]], [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]], [[Cuenca, Batangas|Cuenca]], [[Ibaan]], [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''5'''\n| style=\"background:{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Vicente Agregado\n| June 3, 1919\n| June 6, 1922\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[5th Philippine Legislature|5th]]\n| [[Nacionalista Party|Nacionalista]]\n| [[1919 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 1919]].\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1919\u20131928'''<br/>[[Alitagtag]], [[Batangas City|Batangas]], [[Bauan, Batangas|Bauan]], [[Cuenca, Batangas|Cuenca]], [[Ibaan]], [[Mabini, Batangas|Mabini]], [[San Luis, Batangas|San Luis]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''6'''\n| style=\"background:{{Nacionalista Party/meta/color}};\" | \n| Rafael Villanueva\n| June 6, 1922\n| June 